            <div class="feature_wrapper option1">
                <div class="section_header">
                    <h3>Overview</h3>
                </div>

                <p>MetricsAt is a cloud-based service, which can measure and monitor any data from your applications. By installing the software, the Metrics At Agent, your data will be automatically collected and sent to our central cluster. Not only will the central cluster provide you with a metric report with graphics efficiently, but the alert system will also notify you of crossing-over thresholds immediately.</p>

                <div class="row feature">
                    <div class="col-sm-8 info">
                        <h3 id="metrics">
                            Collect and Measure Data
                        </h3>
                        <p>
                            Currently we provide three methods to collect your application datum: log files, database queries and shell commands.
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                          <li>Log Files: Monitor your log files, filter and extract data by your specified regular expressions.</li>
                          <li>Database queries: Execute periodically your specified query statements (SQL or Mongo).</li>
                          <li>Shell commands: Periodically run your specified shell commands in your host. (For example, under a directory, you can input <code>ls -1 /you/path/ | wc -l</code> to metric and monitor how many files in the directory).</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-sm-4 info">
                        <h3 id="alert">
                            Alert function
                        </h3>
                        <p>
                            If thresholds are crossed over, the Alert function will notify you automatically by email or  PagerDuty. 
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
